Class CageDataException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • CageDataException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class CageDataException
extends java.lang.Exception
    An exception thrown by the CageData object if parameters are not legal.
    • The cage designation must starts with the letter 'A' of the letter 'B'. The next digits must be a number between 10 and 99 inclusive.
    • The month must be one of the 12 months on the Roman calendar (not abbreviated).
    • Individual daily feed amount values must lie between 0 and 2000kg.
    • The number of feed values in the array must match the number of days in the month for which the data was recorded.
    Version:
    1.0

    Jeremy
